"{\"opportunities\":[{\"name\":\"Supporting Grassroots Music\",\"organization\":\"Arts Council England\",\"funding\":\"\u00a32.5 million total for this financial year\",\"details\":\"The Supporting Grassroots Music fund is part of the UK Government\u2019s Creative Industries Sector Vision, funded by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport. It specifically supports rehearsal and recording studios, festivals, promoters, and venues for live and electronic music performance. This programme is a time-limited priority within National Lottery Project Grants. An additional ring-fenced budget of \u00a31.5 million is available within Project Grants specifically to support the grassroots live music sector.\",\"eligibility\":\"The fund supports rehearsal and recording studios, festivals, promoters, as well as venues for live and electronic music performance.\",\"application_requirements\":\"Applicants are advised to familiarize themselves with all relevant guidance documents and information sheets before starting their application.\",\"other\":\"The programme follows a previous \u00a35 million investment from November 2023 to April 2025. An evaluation of the Supporting Grassroots Live Music fund (2019-2023) helped inform the design of this current programme.\"}]}"